<br>
Once you get beyond the legalese, the landlord is definitely supposed to have the repairs done as soon as possible. If he does not, you can give him written certified notice and have the repair done. If anything happens to your apartment or belongings during the waiting period of getting it fixed (which is in effect even on verbal notice, you can sue for any stolen items etc if they have been at least verbally notified) then they are liable for said items. Since the statute is vague on what constitutes a &quot;reasonable time&quot; I suggest you call the Tenant-Landlord Hotline at 404-206-5343 or 800-369-4706. They should be able to give a closer definition, however I am guessing it probably is 7 days from time of notification.<br>
<br>
Good luck no matter what, and in the meantime maybe you should try to block the door however you can. It sounds silly but if the door opens out, get some rope. If it opens in, a chair under the door might help. Either one is not going to keep a determined person out but it might give you or your sister time to retreat to a safer room and/or call the authorities.<br>
